<subSubSection id="C30F32F2DF15FFEB1EBE8CB32DA1FA52" pageId="18" pageNumber="1423" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAA6179DF15FFEB1EBE8CB32F4EFB5D" blockId="18.[211,309,1164,1188]" box="[211,309,1164,1188]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1423">
<emphasis id="B961BD6BDF15FFEB1EBE8CB32F4EFB5D" box="[211,309,1164,1188]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1423">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA6179DF15FFEB1EBE8C8B2DA1FA52" blockId="18.[211,1172,1203,1451]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1423">
<taxonomicName id="4C151AFADF15FFEB1EBE8C8B2D68FB32" authority="Medvedev and Kantner, 2002" authorityName="Medvedev and Kantner. Moreover" authorityYear="2002" box="[211,787,1203,1228]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aetheomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="1423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcata">
<emphasis id="B961BD6BDF15FFEB1EBE8C8B2FB3FB35" box="[211,456,1204,1228]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1423">Aetheomorpha furcata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF841C88DF15FFEB1FA08C8C2D68FB32" author="Medvedev LN &amp; Kantner F" box="[461,787,1203,1227]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1423" pagination="259 - 269" refId="ref13724" refString="Medvedev LN, Kantner F. 2002. Some new and poorly known Clytrinae (Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae) of the Old World. Entomol Basil. 24: 259 - 269." type="journal article" year="2002">Medvedev and Kantner, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C151AFADF15FFEB1DE58C8B2F6AFB12" authority="(Jacoby, 1892)" baseAuthorityName="Jacoby" baseAuthorityYear="1892" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aetheomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="1423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decemnotata">
<emphasis id="B961BD6BDF15FFEB1DE58C8B2A48FB35" box="[904,1075,1204,1228]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1423">A. decemnotata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF841C88DF15FFEB1A2D8C8C2F72FB12" author="Jacoby M" pageId="18" pageNumber="1423" pagination="869 - 899" refId="ref12748" refString="Jacoby M. 1892. Description of the new genera and species of the phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Sign. L. Fea in Burma. Ann Mus Civic Stor Nat Genova. 32: 869 - 899." type="journal article" year="1892">Jacoby, 1892</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the colour pattern: the pronotum is completely fulvous and elytron is covered with four black spots. The obviously broad bidentate aedeagal apex is a useful character by which to recognize 
<taxonomicName id="4C151AFADF15FFEB1C608D2C2A70FAD2" authority="Medvedev and Kantner. Moreover" authorityName="Medvedev and Kantner. Moreover" authorityYear="2002" box="[525,1035,1299,1323]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aetheomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="1423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcata">
<emphasis id="B961BD6BDF15FFEB1C608D2C2C06FAD2" box="[525,637,1299,1323]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1423">A. furcata</emphasis>
Medvedev and Kantner. Moreover
</taxonomicName>
, this species also has the following characters: vertex and scutellum fulvous, body more slender, spermathecal duct very long, loosely coiled dozens of times with a thickened base. Moreover, the dorsal rectal sclerites are different from those in the other congeneric species, central sclerite is semicircular, lateral ones are sub-triangular.
</paragraph>
